The paper proposes a method for reconstructing parametric maps from magnetic resonance fingerprinting (MRF) data using a spatiotemporal convolutional neural network. This involves exploiting the relationship between neighboring MRF signal evolutions to replace the dictionary matching used in standard MRF reconstruction. Given that the paper involves both image processing and machine learning techniques, it is likely to fall under the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the use of neural networks suggests that it could also be classified under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Finally, the use of magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) data suggests that it could also be classified under Multimedia (cs.MM).
